@NODE "StepBack()" "Debug: StepBack()"

@{b}@{u}FUNCTION@{uu}@{ub}
Name:     StepBack()
Short:    Steps back the debugging tree in IceBreaker.
Synopsis: void StepBack(void)

@{b}@{u}DESCRIPTION@{uu}@{ub}
This function is intended for use by system modules.

StepBack()  is  used  in  conjunction with the Debug structure.  Whenever a
debug  routine  is called, it will be necessary to later call StepBack() in
order to keep the tree display formatted properly.

@EndNode
